cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with face alignment, which is a computer vision problem, hence it is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) category. The paper also uses a 3D deformable model, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.GR (Graphics) category. The use of a cascaded coupled-regressor approach and the evaluation of the algorithm's performance suggest that it may also belong to the cs.MM (Multimedia) category. The paper proposes a novel algorithm that estimates both 2D and 3D landmarks, which involves machine learning techniques, indicating that it may belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) category. Finally, the paper evaluates its algorithm's performance on a large collection of face images, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) category.
